abstract: Jennifer Lynn Wilson, a daughter of Valerie A. Wilson of Bronxville, N.Y., and Robert G. Wilson of Key Biscayne, Fla., was married last evening to Brian Joseph Buttigieg, a son of Mr. and Mrs. Michael Buttigieg of Floral Park, L.I. The Rev. Dr. Robert W. Bedingfield officiated at the Reformed Church in Bronxville.   Mrs. Wilson-Buttigieg, 24 years old, is a vice president of Valerie Wilson Travel, a New York agency owned by her mother. The bride and bridegroom graduated from Haverford College. Her father, formerly a general partner of the New York investment banking firm of Goldman, Sachs & Company, is the chairman and chief executive of Ecologic Waste Services, a landfill renovator in Miami. Her stepmother is Anne C. Wilson of Key Biscayne.

abstract: Valerie Ann Wilson of Bronxville, N.Y., and Robert G. Wilson of Key Biscayne, Fla., have announced the engagement of their daughter Jennifer Lynn Wilson to Brian Joseph Buttigieg, the son of Mr. and Mrs. Michael Buttigieg of Floral Park, L.I. A wedding is planned for June.   Miss Wilson, 23 years old, and her fiance, 24, graduated from Haverford College. She is a vice president of Valerie Wilson Travel in New York, a company owned by her mother. Her father is the chairman of Ecologic Waste Services in Fort Lauderdale, Fla.

abstract: A gilded French 18th-century cabinet, used at Versailles during the reign of Louis XV, sold Sunday in Monte Carlo for 15 million French francs or about $1.6 million.   The ebony and mahogany cabinet, crafted by Guillaume Beneman, a master cabinetmaker, once was owned by Alphonse de Rothschild, of the French banking family.
